class Solution {
    public double new21Game(int n, int k, int maxPts) {
        if (k == 0 || n >= k + maxPts) return 1.0;
        double[] dp = new double[n + 1];
        double probability = 0.0, windowSum = 1.0;
        dp[0] = 1.0;
        for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
            dp[i] = windowSum / maxPts;
            if (i < k) windowSum += dp[i];
            else probability += dp[i];
            if (i >= maxPts) windowSum -= dp[i - maxPts];
        }
        return probability;
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(n)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution uses dynamic programming to store the probabilities of reaching each score from 0 to n. It maintains a sliding window sum to efficiently calculate the probabilities, ensuring a linear time complexity.
